{"clause_type": "right of first refusal, offer or negotiation", "summary": "If the agreement ends and the franchisee doesn't continue running the restaurant, the company (BKC) has the option to:

(a) Buy the restaurant location and/or equipment at a fair price, if the franchisee owns them.

(b) Take over the lease of the restaurant location at a fair price, if the franchisee rents it."}

{"clause_type": "parties", "summary": ""The company, Dragon Systems, is responsible for providing the services and materials outlined in this agreement. These services include regular on-site visits, maintenance, and technical support for the software and hardware provided to the client. Dragon Systems will also offer training sessions for the client's staff to ensure they can effectively use the provided tools. All services will be performed by qualified personnel, and Dragon Systems will adhere to the agreed-upon schedule and service levels. Any changes to the scope of services must be agreed upon in writing by both parties."

**Summary:**

Dragon Systems will provide and maintain certain software and hardware for the client. They promise to visit regularly, provide tech support, and train the client's staff on how to use the tools. All work will be done by qualified people on an agreed schedule. Any changes to the services must be agreed upon in writing by both the company and the client."}

