Paragraph: At the Supplier's option, on termination of this agreement:

(a) the Supplier may buy from the Distributor all or any stocks of Products for the current market value for those Products. The Distributor must deliver such Products to the Supplier within 14 days of receiving the Supplier's notice, and the Supplier must pay for the Products in full within 30 days of their delivery. The Supplier shall be responsible for the costs of packaging, insurance and carriage of the Products; or

(b) the Distributor may dispose of the balance of the Products in its possession and account to the Supplier for the Price for those Products;

{"clause_type": "post-termination services", "summary": "When the agreement ends, the Supplier can choose one of two options:

(a) The Supplier can buy back any remaining products from the Distributor at current market value. The Distributor then has 14 days to return these products, and the Supplier will pay for them within 30 days. The Supplier covers the costs of packing, insuring, and shipping these products.

(b) The Distributor can sell the remaining products and pay the Supplier the agreed-upon price for them."}

Paragraph: During the applicable Exclusive Period, SFJ shall not, and shall cause its Affiliates not to, either by itself or through a Third Party, conduct human clinical trials of, or sell, offer for sale or have sold:

3.19.1 any Competing Product (other than Product) alone or in combination (whether fixed dose or co-packaged) with one (1) or more other active ingredients;

3.19.2 any combination (whether fixed dose or co-packaged) with one (1) or more other active ingredients of the Product and a Competing Product;

3.19.3 any agent that is intended as an antidote to, or is intended to neutralize, abrogate or reverse the antiplatelet activity of, (i) any Brilinta Competing Product alone or in combination (whether fixed dose or co-packaged) with one (1) or more other active ingredients or (ii) both the Ticagrelor Compound and a Brilinta Competing Product;

3.19.4 without limitation to the foregoing, any agent with dual activity as (i) an antidote to, or for use as an agent to neutralize, abrogate or reverse the antiplatelet activity of, the Ticagrelor Compound and (ii) an antidote to, or for use as an agent to neutralize, abrogate or reverse the antiplatelet activity of, any Brilinta Competing Product; or

3.19.5 any Brilinta Competing Product.

{"clause_type": "competitive restriction exception", "summary": "The Agent agrees that during a certain period, it won't be involved in any competing business. However, this rule doesn't apply if:
- the actions are allowed under the agreement;
- the actions relate to specific products listed in Exhibit D or additional agreed products;
- the Agent's interest in a competing business is 5% or less; or
- there's a separate agreement with Monsanto about sharing technology."}

{"clause_type": "revenue/profit sharing", "summary": "The clause means that instead of paying annual royalties in cash, there's an option to convert these royalties into shares of TDA common stock at a rate of $10 of stock for every $1 of royalty. The price of the TDA stock is determined by the average daily price over the previous six months. However, there are two conditions:

1. Only 50% of the total outstanding TDA stock can be issued.
2. If this option is used, it must be done while the agreement is still valid."}

{"clause_type": "parties", "summary": ""Any notice or communication required or permitted to be given under this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be delivered by hand, or mailed by certified or registered mail, postage prepaid, or sent by nationally recognized overnight courier service, or sent by facsimile or electronic mail, with confirmation of receipt..."

Simplified:
"All official messages or papers must be in writing and sent by hand, mail, courier, fax, or email with confirmation.""}

